        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 26 at 3:30PM PDT by NWS Portland OR</headline>
        <description>At 329 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Johnston Ridge Visitors Center, or 9 miles northeast of
Mount St. Helens, moving west at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coldwater Ridge Visitors Center, Johnston Ridge Visitors Center,
Spirit Lake, and Coldwater Lake.

In Washington this includes State Route 504 between mile markers 38
and 51.
</description>
        <instruction>If on or near Coldwater Lake, get out of the water and move indoors
or inside a vehicle. Remember, lightning can strike out to 10 miles
from the parent thunderstorm. If you can hear thunder, you are close
enough to be struck by lightning. Move to safe shelter now! Do not
be caught on the water in a thunderstorm.

Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
this storm passes.</instruction>
